Rating: 3
This delicious dish is worthy of four forks with a few modifications. After burning the ribs in a roasting pan at 350 the first time, I braised them in a covered dutch oven at 300. Add water to the sauce if necessary to fully immerse the ribs. When the ribs are cooked (and succulent!), remove them from the sauce and cover with foil. Then boil the sauce 10-15 minutes to thicken. I also found that 4 lbs of short ribs is the right amount of meat for this much sauce. If you triple the maple syrup and lime juice, they are barely perceptible (instead of totally lost) under the pungent chiles, and the resulting flavor is complex and well-balanced.

